# Plot a `tag` object

This function plots a GeoPressureR `tag` object as a time series or a
map.

By default, `type` is determined in the following order of preference
according to availability: `c("map_pressure", "map_light")`,
`"map_pressure"`, `"map_light"`, `"pressure"`.

`plot.tag()` calls different plotting functions depending on `type`.

- `"pressure"`:
  [`plot_tag_pressure()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot_tag_pressure.md)

- `"light"`:
  [`plot_tag_light()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot_tag_light.md)

- `"acceleration"`:
  [`plot_tag_acceleration()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot_tag_acceleration.md)

- `"temperature"`:
  [`plot_tag_temperature()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot_tag_temperature.md)

- `"twilight"`:
  [`plot_tag_twilight()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot_tag_twilight.md)

- `"actogram"`:
  [`plot_tag_actogram()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot_tag_actogram.md)

- `"map_*"` :
  [`plot.map()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot.map.md)
  with `tag$map_*` as first argument.

Refers to these functions for additional parameters and more flexibility
in the plotting.

## Usage

``` r
# S3 method for class 'tag'
plot(x, type = NULL, ...)
```

## Arguments

- x:

  a GeoPressureR `tag` object.

- type:

  type of the plot to display. One of `"pressure"`, `"acceleration"`,
  `"light"`, `"temperature"`, `"twilight"`, `"actogram"`, `"map"`,
  `"map_pressure"`, `"map_light"`, `"map_pressure_mse"`,
  `"map_pressure_mask"`, `"mask_water"`. Map can be combined by
  providing a vector of type.

- ...:

  additional parameters for
  [`plot_tag_pressure()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot_tag_pressure.md),
  [`plot_tag_acceleration()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot_tag_acceleration.md),
  [`plot_tag_light()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot_tag_light.md),
  [`plot_tag_twilight()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot_tag_twilight.md)
  or
  [`plot.map()`](https://raphaelnussbaumer.com/GeoPressureR/reference/plot.map.md)

## Value

a plot, ggplotly or leaflet object.

## Examples

``` r
withr::with_dir(system.file("extdata", package = "GeoPressureR"), {
  tag <- tag_create("18LX", quiet = TRUE) |>
    tag_label(quiet = TRUE) |>
    twilight_create() |>
    twilight_label_read()
})

# By default, plot will display the time series of pressure
plot(tag)
```
